## Esquema de BD — 16 tablas

### Modificadas
```
users
  + timezone          string IANA, default 'UTC'
  + default_currency  string ISO 4217, default 'USD'  — moneda cuando el usuario no especifica
  + username          string unique nullable            — para descubrimiento de amigos
  + friend_code       string unique                    — hash corto auto-generado, regenerable via tool o web
  + whatsapp_phone    string nullable (fase 2)
```

### Nuevas

```
-- Conversación
conversations
  id, user_id FK, created_at

sessions
  id, conversation_id FK, started_at, last_message_at

messages
  id, conversation_id FK, session_id FK
  role: user | assistant | system | tool_call | tool_result
  channel: web | whatsapp
  content
  actions_json      — opciones clickeables que el frontend renderiza como botones
                      ej: [{ label: "El mismo día", value: "same_day" }, ...]
  metadata_json     — refs mínimas (reminder_request_id, event_id, etc.)
                      para mensajes de audio: { transcription: "..." }
                      para mensajes de imagen: { description: "...", media_id: "..." }
  memory_processed  bool default false
  created_at
  -- adjuntos (audio, imagen, documento) via Spatie Media Library (morphs)

  -- Procesamiento multimodal (ocurre antes de pasar al LLM):
  -- Audio  → el worker transcribe y guarda transcripción en metadata_json.transcription
  -- Imagen → el worker extrae descripción vía vision y la guarda en metadata_json.description;
  --           el LLM puede llamar look_at_image(media_id) para ver la imagen directamente

-- Memoria
memories
  id, user_id FK
  category     string
  description  string (max 2 frases)
  content      text (markdown comprimido)
  updated_at, created_at

-- Eventos
events
  id, user_id FK
  content, event_at  datetime UTC
  event_end          datetime UTC nullable  — para bloques de tiempo con duración (ej: clase 2-4pm)
  type               string (ref soft a type_catalogs)
  recurrence_rule    string nullable
  status             enum: active | cancelled | completed
  sender_id          FK users nullable (si lo envió un amigo)
  referenceable_type string nullable  — morph: clase PHP del modelo referenciado
  referenceable_id   string nullable  — morph: ID del modelo referenciado
  created_at, updated_at
  -- alias legibles via MorphTypeMap: 'list' → AssistantList, 'expense' → Expense

event_reminders
  id, event_id FK
  fire_at datetime UTC
  message string
  status  enum: pending | fired | failed
  fired_at datetime nullable

-- Listas
lists
  id, user_id FK (dueño)
  name, type    string (ref soft a type_catalogs)
  created_at, updated_at

list_items
  id, list_id FK
  content, status enum: pending | done
  position int
  added_by_user_id FK users
  created_at, updated_at

-- Catálogo de tipos
type_catalogs
  id
  user_id FK nullable   — null = tipo global del sistema
  domain  enum: event | list | expense
  name    string
  UNIQUE(user_id, domain, name)

-- Gastos
expenses
  id, user_id FK
  amount_cents  integer            — almacenado en centavos
  currency      string ISO 4217    — detectada del mensaje; si no se especifica, usa users.default_currency
  description   string
  type          string nullable     — ref soft a type_catalogs (domain=expense)
  spent_at      datetime UTC
  created_at, updated_at

-- Red de amigos
friendships
  id
  requester_id FK users
  addressee_id FK users
  status enum: pending | accepted | declined | blocked
  created_at, updated_at
  UNIQUE(requester_id, addressee_id)

friend_labels
  id
  user_id        FK users   — quien pone el apodo
  friend_user_id FK users   — a quién se lo pone
  label string
  created_at, updated_at
  UNIQUE(user_id, friend_user_id)

friend_categories
  id
  user_id FK users
  name string
  created_at, updated_at
  UNIQUE(user_id, name)

friend_category_members
  category_id    FK friend_categories
  friend_user_id FK users
  created_at
  PRIMARY KEY (category_id, friend_user_id)

-- Colaboración
list_shares
  id
  list_id              FK lists
  shared_with_user_id  FK users
  invited_by_user_id   FK users
  permission           enum: read | write
  accepted_at          datetime nullable
  created_at

reminder_requests
  id
  sender_id        FK users
  receiver_id      FK users
  content          string
  suggested_event_at datetime nullable
  status           enum: pending | accepted | declined
  event_id         FK events nullable   — se llena al aceptar
  message_id       FK messages nullable — el mensaje mostrado al receptor
  created_at, updated_at
```

